                           Stude nt Investigations


   GLOBE students understand the importance of creating hypotheses,
   analyzing data, drawing conclusions a nd reporting their results. This
   scientific process allows others to build on their findings. GLOBE
   Student Investigations are reports of scientific projects and
   activities conducted by GLOBE stud ents using GLOBE data. GLOBE schools
   are encouraged to collaborate in one of the many School to School
   Activities.

                               Submit a Report
                             Archive of Reports

   The State Of Radunia Canal Water The State Of Radunia Canal Water by
   Students of the last 2grades of Environment Protection Classes
   Complex of Engineering and Environmental Protection Schools
   The students made research of quality of the local rivier finding out
   that the recent pro-environment activities in the region really helped.
   BLACK MAP of LABIN AREA BLACK MAP of LABIN AREA by ALEN OKANOVIC &
   GPS-GROUP
   Srednja skola Mate Blazine Labin
   ASSIGNMANT OF OUR WORK WAS TO LOCATE WILD RRUBISH-HEAPS IN LABIN AREA,
   DRAW BLACK MAP, DETERMINE THE TYPE OF GARBAGE AND IT*S QUANTITY AND
   INFORM LOCAL GOVERMENT, TOURISTZ ASSOCIATION OF LABIN AND THE WHOLE
   COMMUNITY ABOUT THE COURENT CONDITIONS OF OUR ENVIROMENT WITH A GOAL TO
   INITIATE SOME ACTIONS THAT WOULD LEAD TO THE IMPROVEMENT OF THE
   SANITARY CONDITIONS.

   WE HAVE LOCATED 135 RRUBISH-HEAPS AND TWO MONTHS AFTER INFORMING LOCAL
   GOVERMENT ONCE AGAIN OUR TEAM VISITED THE SAME PLACE TO CHEK IF THEY
   MADE ANY MOVES TO IMPROVE OUR ENVIROMENT SO FAR HAS BEEN FIXED WHICH
   ISN*T MUCH , BUT GIVES US HOPE TO KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK WITH GOAL OF
   SUCCEDING OUR MISSION. PROTECT TODAY-TO HAVE BETTER TOMORROW
   Rocky Mountain National Park Field Study Rocky Mountain National Park
   Field Study by Alexander Dawson School
   Alexander Dawson School
   On April 27, 2001 we conducted a field study in a moraine in the
   mountains of Colorado. We used protocols for soil, land cover and
   hydrology to make our observations.
